## Confluence Page 1: VM Log Shipping
```
Page Title: Log Shipping | VM → Fluent Bit → Splunk HEC
Parent:     Platform Engineering / Observability / Log Shipping
Labels:     fluent-bit, splunk, vm, windows, rhel, terraform
```

***
### Overview
This page documents the solution for shipping logs from Azure Virtual Machines (Windows and Linux/RHEL) directly to Splunk using **Fluent Bit** as the log shipper via the **Splunk HTTP Event Collector (HEC)**.

| Property | Value |
|----------|-------|
| **Log Shipper** | Fluent Bit 3.2.7 |
| **Deployment Method** | Azure VM Extension |
| **Destination** | Splunk HEC `:8088` |
| **Splunk Index** | `vm-logs` |
| **Protocol** | HTTPS + TLS + gzip |
| **Status** | ✅ Production |

***
### Architecture
> *(Attach diagram_vm.png here)*

```
Windows VMs  →  Azure Extension (Microsoft.Compute / CustomScriptExtension v1.10)
                      → Fluent Bit (Windows Service)
                            → Splunk HEC :8088 (index=vm-logs)

RHEL/Linux VMs → Azure Extension (Microsoft.Azure.Extensions / CustomScript v2.1)
                      → Fluent Bit (systemd service)
                            → Splunk HEC :8088 (index=vm-logs)
```

***
### Azure Extension Details
| OS | Publisher | Type | Version |
|----|-----------|------|---------|
| **Windows** | `Microsoft.Compute` | `CustomScriptExtension` | `1.10` |
| **Linux / RHEL** | `Microsoft.Azure.Extensions` | `CustomScript` | `2.1` |

> ⚠️ **Important:** Azure Extensions are OS-specific. Using the wrong publisher will cause the extension to fail silently.

***
### Log Sources Collected
**Windows VMs:**
| Source | Path / Channel | Fluent Bit Tag |
|--------|---------------|----------------|
| Application log files | `C:\logs\siem\*.log` | `vm.filelogs` |
| IIS logs | `C:\inetpub\logs\*.log` | `vm.filelogs` |
| Windows Event Log | `Security, System, Application` | `vm.winevents` |

**Linux / RHEL VMs:**
| Source | Path | Fluent Bit Tag |
|--------|------|----------------|
| SIEM/App logs | `/var/log/siem/*.log` | `vm.applogs` |
| Systemd journal | systemd unit logs | `vm.syslog` |
| Auth/Secure logs | `/var/log/secure` | `vm.secure` |

***
### Terraform Module Structure
```
modules/
├── fluentbit-vm/
│   ├── main.tf                   ← Extension resources (for_each)
│   ├── variables.tf              ← Inputs: vm_ids, splunk_hec_*
│   └── scripts/
│       ├── install-linux.sh      ← RHEL/Ubuntu install + config
│       └── install-windows.ps1   ← Windows install + service setup
└── vm/
    └── main.tf                   ← YOUR EXISTING MODULE (add module call)
```

**Scaling:** Uses `for_each` on `linux_vm_ids` and `windows_vm_ids` maps.
Adding a new VM = add one line to `terraform.tfvars`. Zero code changes.

***
### Required Variables (`terraform.tfvars`)
```hcl
splunk_hec_host  = "splunk.yourcompany.com"
splunk_hec_port  = 8088
splunk_hec_token = "xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx"   # ← from Splunk UI

linux_vm_ids = {
  "vm-rhel-prod-01" = "/subscriptions/.../vm-rhel-prod-01"
  "vm-rhel-prod-02" = "/subscriptions/.../vm-rhel-prod-02"
}

windows_vm_ids = {
  "vm-win-prod-01" = "/subscriptions/.../vm-win-prod-01"
}
```

***
### Deployment Steps
1. Enable Splunk HEC → `Settings → Data Inputs → HTTP Event Collector → New Token`
2. Create index `vm-logs` in Splunk
3. Add `splunk_hec_*` variables to `terraform.tfvars`
4. Add module call to `modules/vm/main.tf`
5. Run `terraform init && terraform plan && terraform apply`
6. Verify: `VM → Extensions + applications → fluentbit-linux/windows = Succeeded`

***
### Verification Commands
```bash
# Linux/RHEL
sudo systemctl status fluent-bit
sudo journalctl -u fluent-bit -f

# Windows (PowerShell)
Get-Service FluentBit
Get-EventLog -LogName Application -Source FluentBit -Newest 20

# Splunk search
index=vm-logs source=azure-vm-linux
index=vm-logs source=azure-vm-windows
```

***
### Troubleshooting
| Symptom | Cause | Fix |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Extension status = Failed | Wrong publisher for OS | Check publisher matches OS table above |
| No logs in Splunk | HEC token wrong | Verify token in `terraform.tfvars` |
| Extension already exists | Previous deploy | `terraform taint` the extension resource |
| TLS error | Self-signed cert | Set `TLS.Verify Off` in Fluent Bit config |

